"The arguments pseudo array becomes a little bit more array-like in ES5. In strict mode, it loses its callee and caller properties."<p>Anyone know what replaces this?<p>How would I write this (stupid code that would eventually blow the stack) without arguments.callee?<p><pre><code>    (function () {
        console.log("hello world");
        setTimeout(arguments.callee, 1000);
    })();</code></pre>
